<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>A setLifeTime() method would be very-very handful to change the lifetime without initialize a new cache object. At the moment we must have as much cache object as much lifetime we want use instead of using one cache object.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if(!$cache-&gt;start('mypage')) {
        echo 'This is cached with init lifetime ('.time().') ';
        $cache-&gt;end(); 
}

$cache-&gt;setLifeTime( 3 );

if(!$cache-&gt;start('mypage2')) {
        echo 'This is cached with 3 seconds lifetime ('.time().') ';
        $cache-&gt;end();
}
</code></pre>

